# x-agent Exploration Notes

## Key Files & Roles
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/AGENTS.md`: repository-level constraints and required conventions.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared boilerplate used by all agents (env defaults, setup, output contract helpers, lock handling).
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/run-scenarios.sh`: scenario harness that discovers `scenario.env`, enforces `REQUIRED_TOOLS`, and runs scripts from fixture directories.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/kube-agent/` (to be created): new kube validator agent implementation.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh`: prior art for chart/CHANGED_FILES discovery and Step/Result contract.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh`: prior art for scoped discovery and all-scope SKIP semantics.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/kube-agent/SKILL.md` (to be created): trigger language and allowed tool declarations.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/install.sh`: installer matrix, skill discovery, dependency checks, and snippet generation.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/README.md`: agent catalog and usage examples.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/clean/` and `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/issues/` (to be created): scenario fixtures for pass/fail baseline coverage.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/specs/07-kube-agent.md`: acceptance and FR map for this spec.

## Patterns & Conventions
- Every runnable agent starts with `#!/usr/bin/env bash` and `set -euo pipefail`.
- Shared lib contract from `lib/x-agent-common.sh` is used for Step framing, output timing, `FAIL_FAST`, cleanup trap, and lock support.
- Output contract requires `Step`, `Result`, optional `Fix`, `Full log` and final `Overall`.
- `--help`/`help`/`-h` must work before dependency checks.
- `CHANGED_FILES` scope is optional but required when meaningful.
- `install.sh` lists `SKILLS`, performs optional dependency checks only for selected skills, and installs `lib/` with local symlink or remote copy.
- `README.md` and `SKILL.md` must be updated for new agents to keep discoverability and invocation metadata consistent.

## Database Schema
No database is used in this repository.

## Test Infrastructure
- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` runs shellcheck first and then each `scenario.env` fixture.
- `scenario.env` contract fields: `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, `RUNNER` optional, `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.
- Scenario fixtures can set `CHANGED_FILES` directly inside `scenario.env`; harness will source these variables before execution.
- `REQUIRED_TOOLS` controls skip behavior when external binaries are not present.
- CI runs the same harness for parity.

## Architecture & Data Flow
- Input flow: user command + env -> agent script -> discovery scope (`CHANGED_FILES` or repo walk) -> validation command -> log capture -> standardized result output.
- Dependencies flow from shared lib to command implementations; there is no cross-agent runtime dependency.
- Validation output is intentionally truncated in the terminal but fully retained in temporary OUTDIR log files.

## Planned Integration Points for Kube Agent
- `skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh` should follow `helm-agent`/`gha-agent` dispatch patterns.
- `tests/kube-agent` should include clean/issues plus at least one scoped and one no-manifest scenario for explicit FR-3 validation.
- `install.sh` should register `kube-agent` in `SKILLS`, dependency warning checks, and AGENTS snippet line.
- `README.md` should include a short usage section mirroring existing agent style.
- `skills/kube-agent/SKILL.md` should include `KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR`, `RUN_VALIDATE`, and universal knob patterns.
