A /Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md
# x-agent Exploration Notes

## Key Files & Roles
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/AGENTS.md`: repository conventions, output contract, and required knobs.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared Bash helpers for step/timing output, defaults, lock, logging, and cleanup behavior.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/run-scenarios.sh`: orchestrates shellcheck plus all fixture runs.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh`: scoped discovery and skip behavior reference.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh`: chart discovery, multi-target dispatch, and command wiring reference.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`: large step implementation and optional-tool handling reference.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/specs/07-kube-agent.md`: acceptance criteria and implementation contract for kube validation.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/kube-agent/SKILL.md` (to be created): trigger metadata and allowed tool declarations.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh` (to be created): kubeconform/kubeval driver.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/clean/` (to be created): passing manifest fixture and expected clean path.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/issues/` (to be created): invalid manifest fixture and expected failure path.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/install.sh`: skill registration, optional dependency checks, and AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet output.
- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/README.md`: catalog/usage documentation location.

## Patterns & Conventions
- All scripts are Bash with `set -euo pipefail` and helper-driven output framing.
- `--help`/`help`/`-h` must be parsed before tool checks and project assumptions.
- `need` for hard dependencies exits with code 2 and user-facing message.
- `setup_outdir` and `print_result` are used for standardized log handling and contract compliance.
- `MAX_LINES` behavior defaults to 40 locally and 999999 in CI.
- `RUN_<STEP>`, `KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, `FAIL_FAST`, `CHANGED_FILES`, `TMPDIR_ROOT` are universal knobs.
- `SKILL.md` `allowed-tools` includes every environment knob and the agent command path.
- `RESULT: FAIL` lines must include `Fix:` hints; SKIP is allowed for missing optional dependencies or no-op scope.
- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` skips scenarios when a required tool is missing and expects `EXPECT_EXIT` for non-skipped runs.

## Database Schema
- No SQL/NoSQL schema exists for runtime agent operation.
- Metadata used by RALPH is file-based (`.ralph/` state/log files) and not part of the runtime checks here.

## Test Infrastructure
- Test entrypoint: `tests/run-scenarios.sh`.
- Shellcheck runs on all scripts in `skills/`, `lib/`, and root/test scripts before fixtures by default.
- Fixture contract in `scenario.env`: `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, optional `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.
- `CHANGED_FILES` can be injected from `scenario.env` for scoped execution validation.
- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` compares fixture output only by exit code and prints logs for failures.
- Additional fixtures are recommended where FRs require scoped discovery and skip paths, especially for `CHANGED_FILES`.

## Architecture & Data Flow
- Input: environment + args -> argument parser -> dependency resolution -> discovery -> command execution -> logged output + structured step status -> overall result.
- Shared library functions are imported by each agent script and provide deterministic output/cleanup contract.
- kube-agent architecture must remain isolated: no mutable shared artifacts beyond temp logs and existing working directory reads.
- Validation commands are external to repo and called per discovered manifest set with result aggregation in script state.
- Outputs go through shared formatting and are also persisted in `OUTDIR` for detailed failure inspection.

## Planned Integration for Spec 07
- Implement `skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh` with validator selection at startup and manifest discovery with scoped/no-match behavior.
- Build `tests/kube-agent/clean/` and `tests/kube-agent/issues/` fixtures plus explicit scoped and no-manifest coverage for FR-3 reliability.
- Add `skills/kube-agent/SKILL.md` with `RUN_VALIDATE`, `KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR`, and universal knob grants.
- Update installer (`install.sh`) to include `kube-agent` skill metadata and optional tool messaging.
- Update `README.md` with agent row, usage section, and direct invocation example.
- Keep this file updated if discovery/scenario/installer patterns or cross-agent assumptions change during implementation.
